of%20the%20Olympics%2C%20here%20are%20some%20facts%20about%20testosterone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20testosterone%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETestosterone%20is%20a%20sex%20hormone%20produced%20by%20both%20men%20and%20women.%20However%20men%20produce%20up%20to%2020%20times%20more%20testosterone%20--%20primarily%20in%20the%20testicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20make%20far%20less%2C%20in%20the%20ovaries%20and%20adrenal%20glands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20normal%20level%20of%20testosterone%20for%20men%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%2010%20to%2035%20nanomoles%20per%20litre%20in%20blood%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Mount%20Sinai%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20women%2C%20it%20is%20between%200.5%20to%202.4%20nmol%20per%20litre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETestosterone%20levels%20can%20also%20vary%20widely%20by%20age%20and%20time%20of%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20naturally%20produce%20an%20excess%20of%20sex%20hormones%20such%20as%20testosterone%2C%20it%20is%20called%20hyperandrogenism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20condition%20affects%20an%20estimated%20five%20percent%20of%20women%2C%20with%20around%2070%20percent%20of%20cases%20caused%20by%20polycystic%20ovary%20syndrome%2C%20research%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESymptoms%20include%20acne%2C%20body%20hair%20growth%20and%20scalp%20hair%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20this%20affect%20sport%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETestosterone%20can%20promote%20bone%20and%20muscle%20mass%20--%20deliberately%20boosting%20levels%20is%20a%20common%20form%20of%20doping%20and%20is%20banned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20suggested%20that%20people%20with%20an%20excess%20of%20testosterone%20are%20over-represented%20in%20elite%20sport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20how%20much%20the%20hormone%20boosts%20performance%20remains%20a%20matter%20of%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Olympic%20Committee's%20head%20of%20human%20rights%20Magali%20Martowicz%20said%20in%202021%20that%20there%20no%20was%20no%20%26quot%3Bscientific%20consensus%26quot%3B%20on%20how%20testosterone%20affects%20athletic%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%202021%20Tokyo%20Games%2C%20New%20Zealand%20weightlifter%20Laurel%20Hubbard%20became%20the%20first%20openly%20transgender%20woman%20to%20take%20part%20in%20an%20Olympic%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20qualify%2C%20she%20had%20to%20keep%20her%20testosterone%20levels%20below%2010%20nmol%20per%20litre%20for%20at%20least%2012%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20spite%20of%20meeting%20the%20requirements%2C%20Hubbard's%20participation%20was%20widely%20criticised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20the%20IOC%20gave%20up%20on%20establishing%20uniform%20guidelines%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20participation%20criteria%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20the%20separate%20international%20sport%20federations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20the%20boxers%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhelif%20was%20disqualified%20during%20the%20boxing%20world%20championships%20last%20year%20after%20%26quot%3Belevated%20levels%20of%20testosterone%20failed%20to%20meet%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20IOC's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhelif%20and%20boxer%20Taiwan's%20Lin%20Yu-ting%20were%20both%20disqualified%20from%20the%20New%20Delhi%20event%20by%20the%20International%20Boxing%20Association%20(IBA)%20under%20Russian%20oligarch%20Umar%20Kremlev.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%20because%20of%20governance%2C%20financial%20and%20ethical%20issues%20at%20the%20IBA%2C%20it%20was%20effectively%20expelled%20from%20the%20Olympic%20movement%20last%20year.%20The%20IOC%20has%20taken%20responsibility%20for%20organising%20the%20boxing%20at%20the%20Paris%20Games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20IBA%20said%20the%20two%20boxers%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20undergo%20a%20testosterone%20examination%20but%20were%20subject%20to%20a%20separate%20and%20recognised%20test%2C%20whereby%20the%20specifics%20remain%20confidential%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIOC%20spokesman%20Mark%20Adams%20said%20everyone%20taking%20part%20in%20the%20women's%20event%20was%20%26quot%3Bcomplying%20with%20competition%20eligibility%20rules%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20athletes%20have%20competed%20many%20times%20before%20for%20many%20years%2C%20they%20haven't%20just%20arrived%2C%20they%20competed%20in%20Tokyo%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTestosterone%20is%20not%20a%20perfect%20test.%20Many%20women%20can%20have%20testosterone%20which%20is%20in%20what%20would%20be%20called%20'male%20levels'%20and%20still%20be%20women%2C%20still%20compete%20as%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20that%20suddenly%20you%20do%20one%20test%20for%20testosterone%20and%20that%20sorts%20everything%20out%20--%20not%20the%20case%2C%20I'm%20afraid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20we're%20all%20agreed%20that%20we're%20not%20calling%20for%20people%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20bad%20old%20days%20of%20sex%20testing%2C%20which%20was%20a%20terrible%20thing%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722684540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fi63gi7b8_imane-khelif-afp_625x300_02_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Folympics-why-is-algerian-boxer-imane-khelif-embroiled-in-gender-row-being-called-biological-male-explained-6246580%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Algerian%20boxer%20Imane%20Khelif's%20swift%20defeat%20of%20her%20Italian%20opponent%20at%20the%20Paris%20Olympics%20on%20Thursday%20has%20sparked%20a%20row%20after%20she%20was%20disqualified%20from%20a%20previous%20competition%20over%20reportedly%20hi