m%2Fkamala-harris-might-trigger-trumps-biggest-vulnerability-women-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20historic%20string%20of%20misogynistic%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20questions%20of%20gender%20have%20pulsed%20under%20this%20election%20cycle.%20But%20when%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-address-pass-the-torch-oval-office-harris-election-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edropped%20his%20bid%20for%20reelection%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Harris%20became%20the%20Democratic%20nominee%2C%20those%20questions%20moved%20into%20an%20unavoidable%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e809b95a-9419-4294-9417-f615c1924e44%5C%22%3ETrump's%20%26quot%3Bloud%20aesthetic%26quot%3B%20contrasts%20Harris'%20more%20muted%20styling.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClothing%20and%20image%20have%20always%20been%20an%20important%20part%20of%20politics%2C%20going%20all%20the%20way%20back%20to%20the%20earliest%20days%20of%20the%20English%20monarchy%2C%20said%20Derek%20Guy%2C%20a%20menswear%20writer%20best%20known%20for%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fdieworkwear-interview-menswear-guy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopular%20Twitter%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20traditionally%20masculine%20suit%20has%20been%20and%20still%20is%20a%20fixture%20of%20the%20American%20political%20scene.%20And%20in%20that%20scene%2C%20which%20has%20long%20been%20visually%20and%20literally%20male%2C%20Harris%20has%20had%20to%20carve%20out%20a%20place%20for%20herself%20as%20a%20woman%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20question%20of%20gender%20in%20the%20political%20space%20would%20be%20more%20about%20how%20dress%20has%20changed%20as%20women%20have%20entered%20it%20and%20how%20they've%20either%20adopted%20or%20challenged%20the%20masculine%20uniform%20of%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Guy%20said.%20For%20Harris%2C%20that%20has%20taken%20the%20form%20of%20a%20subdued%20but%20recognizable%20femininity%2C%20experts%20who%20study%20political%20science%20and%20fashion%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20tailored%20the%20traditional%20masculine%20suit%20to%20fit%20both%20his%20body%20and%20his%20brand.%20Guy%20said%20that%20Trump%20often%20wears%20navy%20blue%20Brioni%20suits%2C%20which%20are%20reminiscent%20of%201980s%20power%20silhouettes.%20The%20shoulders%20are%20padded%20and%20extended%20to%20give%20him%20a%20slimmer%2C%20more%20masculine%20figure.%20Around%20his%20neck%2C%20Trump%20opts%20for%20a%20shiny%2C%20satin%2C%20bright%20red%20tie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%2C%20according%20to%20Guy%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bloud%20aesthetic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20far%20from%20loud%20in%20her%20clothing.%20Sparsha%20Saha%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Harvard%20who%20is%20co-authoring%20a%20book%20on%20the%20political%20meanings%20and%20effects%20of%20dress%20styles%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bunremarkable%2C%20but%20also%20feminine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20women%20in%20male-dominated%20fields%2C%20styling%20is%20often%20an%20attempt%20to%20prove%20worthiness%20and%20authority%2C%20said%20Shauna%20Shames%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Rutgers%20University%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20upcoming%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EDressing%20for%20Sex%3A%20The%20Democratic%20Paradox%20Revealed%20by%20Clothes%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20female%20politicians%20will%20start%20with%20an%20assumption%20of%20credentialing%2C%20showing%20that%20they%20are%20competent%2C%26quot%3B%20Shames%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20clothing%20is%20a%20good%20signaling%20device%20to%20show%20competence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Harris%20campaign%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20campaign%20celebrated%20his%20styling%20choices%2C%20as%20spokesperson%20Steven%20Cheung%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20has%20the%20most%20style%20of%20any%20President%20in%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8caa152-d8d6-405a-be7c-e7c11ea2021c%5C%22%3EAn%20old%20controversy%20reinforced%20the%20importance%20of%20styling.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Harris%2C%20the%20attempt%20at%20%26quot%3Bcredentialing%26quot%3B%20has%20meant%20looking%20like%20a%20lawyer%20at%20a%20high-profile%20firm.%20She%20often%20wears%20designer%20pantsuits%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fstyle%2Ffashion%2F2024%2F07%2F23%2Fkamala-harris-fashion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditionally%20safe%20colors%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20neutral%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F28%2Fstyle%2Fkamala-harris-jill-biden-style.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManolo%20Blahnik%20pumps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20also%20has%20a%20known%20affinity%20for%20Converse%20sneakers.%20In%20a%20nod%20to%20her%20sorority%20at%20a%20historically%20Black%20college%2C%20Harris%20will%20typically%20don%20a%20string%20of%20pearls.%20For%20significant%20events%2C%20like%20the%20inauguration%2C%20she'll%20sometimes%20wear%20clothing%20by%20Black%20designers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Shames%2C%20the%20whole%20look%20incorporates%20traditional%20femininity%20and%20perceived%20professionalism%2C%20which%20is%20often%20coded%20as%20male%20and%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaintaining%20the%20feminine%20look%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20strategic%2C%20while%20balancing%20being%20a%20professional%20woman%2C%20a%20woman%20on%20the%20go%2C%20a%20lawyer%2C%26quot%3B%20Saha%20said.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20tough.%20She%20wants%20to%20send%20all%20of%20those%20things%20across%20and%20I%20think%20so%20far%20she's%20done%20that%20very%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20has%20developed%20an%20image%20that%20is%20incredibly%20powerful%20but%20also%20is%20not%20trying%20to%20erase%20her%20femininity%2C%26quot%3B%20Joseph%20Altuzarra%2C%20the%20designer%20behind%20many%20of%20Harris'%20pantsuits%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F28%2Fstyle%2Fkamala-harris-jill-biden-style.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20faced%20a%20clothing%20controversy%20early%20on%20in%20her%20vice%20presidential%20tenure%2C%20when%20she%20graced%20the%20cover%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvp-harris-felt-wounded-and-belittled-by-vogue-cover-photo-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVogue%20magazine%20in%20her%20own%20jeans%20and%20sneakers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20immediately%20called%20the%20look%20too%20casual%20and%20said%20it%20did%20not%20confer%20enough%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fallout%20likely%20taught%20her%20that%2C%20for%20better%20or%20worse%2C%20styling%20has%20real%20consequences%2C%20Saha%20said.%20Women%20in%20politics%2C%20and%20the%20professional%20space%20generally%2C%20must%20toe%20the%20line%20between%20associating%20with%20masculine%20leadership%20traits%20and%20dressing%20in%20accordance%20with%20expectations%20for%20traditional%20femininity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20called%20a%20double%20bind.%20How%20do%20you%20seem%20feminine%20but%20not%20too%20feminine%3F%26quot%3B%20Saha%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20her%20style.%20I%20think%20her%20clothing%20style%20is%20that.%20Feminine%2C%20but%20not%20too%20feminine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20clothing%20does%20not%20need%20to%20thread%20the%20needle%20in%20the%20same%20way%20%E2%80%94%20indeed%2C%20this%20year's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-might-trigger-trumps-biggest-vulnerability-women-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublican%20National%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaned%20on%20traditionally%20masculine%20tropes.%20Shames%20said%20that%20red%2C%20his%20signature%20color%2C%20encodes%20masculinity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5fde348-d8c1-4e37-b602-0ce35603e183%5C%22%3EClothing%20communicates%20values%20and%20is%20a%20necessary%20consideration.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGuy%2C%20however%2C%20sees%20Trump's%20trademark%20style%20as%20more%20closely%20related%20to%20industry%20than%20gender.%20He%20typically%20wears%20suits%20tailored%20to%20engineer%20a%20classically%20masculine%20physique%2C%20but%20his%20overall%20look%20mainly%20conveys%20the%20wealth%20of%20traditional%20real%20estate%20businessmen.%20Some%20of%20Trump's%20clothing%20choices%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20the%20bright%2C%20shiny%20tie%20%E2%80%94%20fly%20in%20the%20face%20of%20classic%20menswear%2C%20but%20work%20because%20of%20his%20specific%20brand%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20never%20really%20remove%20the%20person's%20styling%20from%20the%20person%20wearing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Guy%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20never%20had%20Trump%2C%20if%20any%20other%20person%20wore%20this%2C%20it%20would%20just%20be%20considered%20cheap%2C%20tacky%2C%20and%20gaudy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20his%20background%20in%20reality%20television%2C%20Saha%20said%20that%20Trump%20understands%20the%20game%20of%20quick%20visual%20communication%20and%20knows%20that%20clothing%20can%20send%20signals%20about%20values.%20Harris%20knows%20the%20same%2C%20Shames%20said.%20Aware%20that%20people%20will%20inevitably%20scrutinize%20her%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20woman%20of%20color%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20wears%20strategic%20outfits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20beautiful%20clothing%20that%20communicates%20competence%2C%20it%20communicates%20sophistication%2C%20but%20it%20does%20not%20distract%20from%20what%20she's%20doing%20or%20saying%2C%26quot%3B%20Shames%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20she%20has%20learned%20that%20she%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20attention.%20She%20can't%20not%20be%20looked%20at%2C%20but%20she%20wants%20to%20minimize%20the%20gaze.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Trump%20has%20rewritten%20the%20political%20